@@ -26,1 +26,1 @@ -import module jdk.httpserver; +import com.sun.net.httpserver.*; @@ -106,9 +106,0 @@ - * @implNote - * Prior to JDK 26, in the JDK default implementation, the {@link HttpExchange} attribute map was - * shared with the enclosing {@link HttpContext}. - * Since JDK 26, by default, exchange attributes are per-exchange and the context attributes must - * be accessed by calling {@link HttpExchange#getHttpContext() getHttpContext()}{@link - * HttpContext#getAttributes() .getAttributes()}.

Set this property to "context" to restore the pre JDK 26 behavior. - * @@ -123,0 +114,8 @@ + * @implNote + * Prior to JDK 26, in the JDK default implementation, the {@link HttpExchange} attribute map was + * shared with the enclosing {@link HttpContext}. + * Since JDK 26, by default, exchange attributes are per-exchange and the context attributes must + * be accessed by calling {@link HttpExchange#getHttpContext() getHttpContext()}{@link + * HttpContext#getAttributes() .getAttributes()}.
